I think NullOrValue is a better name

My thinking was that NullOr reads like the sentence when used as a template

"Null or string"

Maybe that was too subtle.
Maybe a longer name, explaining this a bit more might be better, but 🤷, this is a reasonable name. We have much worse named variables.
NullOrValue seems reasonable if you think it's better.
I think it is slightly better but I'll leave it up to you
I intend on making the change, I just haven't had a chance yet.
Done
Looking for input here.  This class works, but the whole "if it's null, value won't be filled in" is a little subtle.  Anyone have any ideas?

You could see if there is a better name, I think EmptyIfNullOrValue is overkill. 
You have a comment, you have it in the commit msg.
I changed the name.  Hopefully it's enough.

Actually, the other option we could do is to support std::variant.  Something like


std::variant<std::null_t, nlohmann::json::object_t>

That would let us solve this same problem for array of string

std::variant<std::null_t, nlohmann::json::object_t, std::string>


If we wanted to go further, we could even define a type for EmptyObject.  Not sure if people know std::variant any better than an invented NullOr class

> std::variant any better than an invented NullOr class

At least they could google std::variant
let me play around with variant and see what it looks like.

ok, I moved to variant.  The code is more complicated, but it doesn't require people to figure out what the nullor class does.  Variant is more generic and "standard" even if the code is a little worse.
Done. I think this makes the most sense.
